%N A394042 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 - 2/p^3 - 1/p^4 + 2/p^5).
%C A394042 The asymptotic probability that two positive integers selected independently at random are both cubefree numbers (A004709), and their greatest common divisor is a squarefree number (A005117).
%F A394042 Equals (1/zeta(2)) * Product_{p prime} (1 + 1/p^2 - 2/p^3) = A059956 * A330594.
%F A394042 Equals A394041 / zeta(3)^2.
%e A394042 0.672951052727728482264636640701335995948024437122073...
